# Profile Section Conventions

## Account Layout (Reusable)

All inner pages under the profile section (Profile, Verification, Favourites, My Bets) use `AccountLayout` with `AccountSidebar`. The sidebar shows on the left with active state based on `activePage` prop. Use `AccountLayout` with `activePage`, `authUser`, `onNavigate`, `onLogout` for any new inner page.

## Support Options (Keep in Sync)

Support options (Live Chat, Contact Us, Help Center, Share Feedback) are defined in `src/constants/supportOptions.js`. This config is used by:
- **Navbar** profile dropdown
- **ProfilePage** sidebar

When adding or changing support options, update `supportOptions.js` so both stay in sync.

## Page Header

When creating or editing pages that live under the Profile section (e.g. Favourites, My Bets, Verification, Bet Slip), use this header pattern:

1. **Back button**: `ChevronLeft` icon + "Back to Profile" text, with `mb-6`
2. **Title**: Page name (e.g. "Favourites", "My Bets", "Verification") as `h1` on the next line

```jsx
<button
    type="button"
    onClick={onBack}
    className="mb-6 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700 transition hover:text-blue-600"
>
    <ChevronLeft size={18} />
    Back to Profile
</button>
<h1 className="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 md:text-3xl">Page Title</h1>
```
